            "quotes": [],
            "text": "PhoBiHSD: A Hybrid PhoBERT BiLSTM Approach for Detecting Hate Speech in Imbalanced Vietnamese Social Media Texts Doan Viet Thien Graduate Program in Information Technology, Cuu Long University, Vietnam Email: nguyenvietthien@gmail.com Abstract Hate speech detection in Vietnamese social media remains challenging due to severe class imbalance and the informal nature of user-generated text. Existing Vietnamese hate speech studies mainly rely on standard Transformer classifiers and provide limited analysis of hybrid designs for imbalance robustness. This study proposes PhoBiHSD (PhoBERT + BiLSTM + ROS), which combines PhoBERT contextual representations with a BiLSTM sequence layer and systematic train-only imbalance handling. Experiments on the ViHSD benchmark (33,400 annotated comments; three-class classification: Clean, Offensive, Hate) show that PhoBiHSD reaches a Macro-F1 of 0.6556 on the test set, outperforming the PhoBERT + BiLSTM baseline (0.6457) and GPT-4o few-shot prompting (0.6282).",
